com.mostc.pftt.main
Class ConfigUtil

java.lang.Object
  com.mostc.pftt.main.ConfigUtil

public final class ConfigUtil
extends java.lang.Object

Handles loading a configuration (hosts, scenarios, credentials, etc...) from a groovy script. This allows for loading scenarios and hosts without creating a special configuration format, its just executable code.

Author:
Matt Ficken
See Also:
getHosts(groovy.lang.GroovyObject), An example configuration file: hosts() { [ // connect to a host using ssh // // can test multiple operating systems, one host for each OS (so multiple hosts) new SSHHost("192.168.1.1", "administrator", "password01!") ] } scenario_sets() { [ // provide address of a MySQL server new MySQLScenario() ] } configure_smtp(def smtp_client) { // specify smtp server and credentials } configure_ftp_client(def ftp_client) { // specify ftp server and credentials }
